	     Durban – A man was seriously injured in a shooting at the Pietermaritzburg taxi rank on Saturday morning, paramedics said. He was found lying at the entrance to the rank shortly before 07:00 with several gunshot wounds, said ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring. He was placed on advanced life support and rushed to Grey's Provincial Hospital for further treatment. "The motive for this incident is not yet known but local authorities were on scene for further investigations," said Meiring.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  